other_tests.findings: A 9 x 5 x 8 mm hemangioma in the left hepatic lobe, unchanged from prior exam. The liver shows no new focal lesions or textural abnormality. The main portal vein is patent with hepatopetal flow. No ascites. No biliary dilatation. CBD measures 3 mm. Collapsed gallbladder containing stones. Unremarkable pancreas. Spleen measures 10.9 cm with homogeneous echotexture. Unremarkable views of right kidney. Normal appearance of the visualized portions of the aorta and IVC.
